rComments: good course structure. she gives textbook slides instead of her own and doesnt record class so make sure to show up and copy down the capstone questions. read the textbook religiously, ask her for office hours, set up excel templates and write down step procedures for each type of question. everything is open book.
worst prof ever,,, but at least she is as lazy as her students and she doesn't prepare exam questions but googles them lol

She posts all the exercises and answers online which is quite important for me. She also gives a quiz(very easy) as a bonus to boost your grade. Just make sure you are able to solve all her exercises, you will receive an easy A.

Worst prof at Telfer. Please avoid if you can. Doesnt really care about her students and doesnt explain concepts. She just puts up her answers to practice questions without actually teaching it. Had to teach myself the whole course from the textbook.

One of the best profs I have ever had. Really wants her students to succeed and will hold extra review sessions if needed. Does a ton of practice questions that are similar to those on quizzes and exams. I would highly recommend taking her!
